Two separate issues here:

**1. `StaticResource` doesn't update at runtime.** Use `DynamicResource` instead — it re-evaluates when the underlying resource changes.

```xml
<!-- ❌ Won't update -->
<Label TextColor="{StaticResource PrimaryTextColor}" />

<!-- ✅ Will update -->
<Label TextColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryTextColor}" />
```

Then swap themes by clearing and merging dictionaries:

```csharp
var mergedDicts = Application.Current.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
mergedDicts.Clear();
mergedDicts.Add(new DarkTheme()); // or LightTheme
```

**2. Android restarts the Activity on `uiMode` change.** Handle it yourself in `MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
[Activity(
    Theme = "@style/Maui.SplashTheme",
    ConfigurationChanges = ConfigChanges.UiMode | ConfigChanges.ScreenSize | ConfigChanges.Orientation
)]
public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
}
```

`ConfigChanges.UiMode` tells Android *not* to destroy/recreate the Activity when dark mode toggles. You can then detect the change and swap your theme:

```csharp
public override void OnConfigurationChanged(Configuration newConfig)
{
    base.OnConfigurationChanged(newConfig);

    bool isDark = (newConfig.UiMode & UiMode.NightMask) == UiMode.NightYes;
    // swap your ResourceDictionary here
}
```

**TL;DR** — `StaticResource` → `DynamicResource` for all theme-bound values, and add `ConfigChanges.UiMode` to prevent the Activity restart.
